<p>A sports psychologist is interested in the relationship between the degree of training and the resting heart rate. In a random sample of 15 cyclists, she finds a correlation of r = .50.</p>
<p>What is the null hypothesis when the presence of a correlation is tested?</p>
</p>]]></text>
